- id: iss-019-s3-union
  title: 'Step 3: Dimensions::union + proptest invariants [HIGHEST RISK] (FINDING-1/6/7)'
  status: done
  description: |-
    ⚠️ **HIGHEST RISK STEP IN THIS REFACTOR.** design §11 explicitly flags this as "pin it down first" — get union logic and proptest invariants locked before any integration work downstream. Failure here cascades into every merge operation in Steps 5/5.5/5.9.

    **Signature (from design §5.1):**
    ```rust
    impl Dimensions {
        pub fn union(self, other: Dimensions, weights: MergeWeights) -> Dimensions;
    }

    pub struct MergeWeights {
        pub existing_importance: f64,
        pub incoming_importance: f64,
    }
    ```

    Note: `self` = existing, `other` = incoming (non-commutative roles).

    **Per-field strategies (design §5.1 — authoritative):**
    - core_fact: longer wins (proxy for fuller extraction)
    - participants: set-union of comma-separated names
    - temporal: higher precision_rank wins (Exact > Range > Day > Vague) — note design lists this ordering
    - location / context / causation / outcome / method: longer wins
    - relations: set-union (semicolon-separated)
    - sentiment: existing wins if present, else incoming (non-commutative)
    - stance: same as sentiment
    - valence: **importance-weighted average** = (a.valence * w.existing_importance + b.valence * w.incoming_importance) / (w.existing + w.incoming), then clamp to [-1.0, 1.0]
    - domain: FINDING-6 rule — (1) concrete beats Other(_), (2) two concretes → existing wins, (3) two Other(_) → longer string wins, tie → existing
    - confidence: min (most cautious) — Uncertain < Likely < Confident for Ord, so min picks lowest
    - tags: BTreeSet union
    - type_weights: per-variant max (affinity never decays)

    **Proptest invariants (mandatory 3, per design §5.3):**
    - idempotence: `a.union(a, weights).eq(&a)` for equal weights
    - associativity: `(a.union(b)).union(c) == a.union(b.union(c))` (modulo consistent weights)
    - monotonicity (information-only-grows): `info_content(union(a,b)) >= max(info_content(a), info_content(b))` where info_content counts Some(_) narrative fields and tags cardinality

    DO NOT assert commutativity — non-commutative by design (sentiment/stance "existing wins").

    **Targeted unit tests for non-commutative cases:**
    - sentiment: Dimensions{sentiment: Some("happy")}.union(Dimensions{sentiment: Some("sad")}) → sentiment = "happy" (existing wins)
    - sentiment: Dimensions{sentiment: None}.union(Dimensions{sentiment: Some("sad")}) → sentiment = "sad" (incoming fills None)
    - stance: same pattern
    - Domain: Coding ∪ Other("foo") = Coding (concrete beats Other)
    - Domain: Coding ∪ Trading = Coding (existing wins among two concretes)
    - Domain: Other("a") ∪ Other("longer") = Other("longer")
    - Domain: Other("same") ∪ Other("same") = Other("same")
    - TemporalMark precision: Vague ∪ Exact = Exact; Day ∪ Range = Range (Range > Day per design)
    - Valence weighted: 0.9 weighted 1.0, -0.3 weighted 0.1 → ≈ 0.79
    - Confidence: Confident ∪ Uncertain = Uncertain (min picks most cautious)
    - info_content: union never has fewer Some narrative fields than existing

    Verify: `cargo test --lib dimensions::union` passes (incl. 3 proptests, default 256 cases each), 0 warnings.

    Design refs: §5.1, §5.3
  priority: 10
  type: task
  metadata:
    design_ref: §5.1, §5.3
    risk_level: highest
